{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1783716661,"nonce":"xMKNh+4IUJGM26eDOoHTgTBGe7s=","message":"Phase 2 progress: **PR 2.3 SQLite view-body introspection MERGED as #98 (squash `4733f97`)**.\n\nPer-backend view-body round-trip is now **complete**: PG (2.1, #96 `1335702`), MySQL (2.2, #97 `0a16df9`), SQLite (2.3, #98 `4733f97`). A squealy-published view re-plans to empty on every backend.\n\n2.3 shipped:\n- `introspect.rs::view()` → `sqlite_master.sql` → `Reader::read_create_view` (SQLite stores the verbatim `CREATE VIEW (cols) AS …`, so the column list is preserved and the reverse parser reconstructs straight from it — no MySQL-style `apply_view_column_names` stamping needed). Missing/un-lowerable → empty `ViewBody::default()` sentinel (graceful; never fails introspection).\n- New squealy-ir walkers: `ViewBody::map_sources` (mutable source walker) and `ViewBody::map_exprs` (exhaustive body-wide `ExprNode` walker).\n- `canonical_view_body` (applied both sides) reconciles three SQLite-specific divergences: schema-qualifier suppression (`SourceRef.schema → None`), the result-pin affinity fold (`invert_sqlite_cast_type(sqlite_affinity(ty))` — SQLite's five affinities are the lossiest cast vocab), and the `LIKE` case-sensitivity flag (SQLite has no `ILIKE`).\n- SQLite plan renderer (`sql.rs::write_plan`): drop + recreate the transitive closure of unchanged \"collateral\" views over a rebuilt/renamed table. 2.3 surfaced this — the body-unknown always-recreate used to pre-drop such views around a rebuild, and making bodies compare-equal removed that protection (SQLite reparses views at `RENAME`).\n\nTests run in-process (no external DB). Local codex clean after 3 rounds (transitive collateral views; the LIKE fold). Subsumes the SQLite view-replan (churn) half of `6a3940a` — commented there; its trigger-wipe half remains under Phase 3.\n\nRemaining Phase-2-adjacent: `1e67ff8` (plumb a fallible runtime render — split off from 2.0d).","files":null}]}